geMIB.name: geMIB
geMIB.contactinfo: postal: DKT A/S Fanoevej 6 DK-4060 Kirke Saaby Denmark email: info@dktcomega.com

geATU.name: geATU
geATU.description: Dumps the Address Translation Unit (ATU) Switch table in semi colon format

geUnicastDelete.name: geUnicastDelete
geUnicastDelete.description: Removes a unicast MAC address from the Address Translation Unit (ATU) Switch table.

geMulticastDelete.name: geMulticastDelete
geMulticastDelete.description: Removes a multicast IP address from the Address Translation Unit (ATU) Switch table.

geIGMPSnooping.name: geIGMPSnooping
geIGMPSnooping.description: Starts/stops IGMP snooping, input parameter 0 = stops IGMP snooping, 1 = starts IGMP snooping. Per Default IGMP snooping is enabled, but has to be configured per port

geVTU.name: geVTU
geVTU.description: Dumps the VLAN Table Unit (VTU) Switch table in semi colon format

geVLANCreate.name: geVLANCreate
geVLANCreate.description: Creates a VLAN, input parameters are: VID:WAN:LAN1:LAN2:LAN3:LAN4:CPU:NRL-ENABLE

geVLANDelete.name: geVLANDelete
geVLANDelete.description: Deletes a VLAN, input parameter is VLAN VID: 0 - 4095

geClearVTU.name: geClearVTU
geClearVTU.description: Clears the VLAN Table Unit (VTU) Switch table, input parameter 1 = clear VTU table

geDumpPIRLBuckets.name: geDumpPIRLBuckets
geDumpPIRLBuckets.description: Dumps a list of the active buckets.

geVLANProviderMode.name: geVLANProviderMode
geVLANProviderMode.description: Enable/disable VLAN provider mode, input parameter 0 = disable VLAN provider mode, 1 = enable VLAN provider mode. Per Default VLAN provider mode is disabled. NOTE: Provider VLAN ID should be setup in port default VID for the originating port.

geCPUPortAutoNegotiation.name: geCPUPortAutoNegotiation
geCPUPortAutoNegotiation.description: Enables/disables auto negotiation on the port. Set to 1 for enable and 0 for disable.

geCPUPortSpeedMode.name: geCPUPortSpeedMode
geCPUPortSpeedMode.description: Sets/gets the speed and duplex mode on the port. Input parameters are: AUTO

geCPUPortLinkStatus.name: geCPUPortLinkStatus
geCPUPortLinkStatus.description: Gets the Link status for the port

geCPUPortFlowControl.name: geCPUPortFlowControl
geCPUPortFlowControl.description: Enables/disables flow control on the port. Set to 1 for enable and 0 for disable.

geCPUPortIEEEQoSPriority.name: geCPUPortIEEEQoSPriority
geCPUPortIEEEQoSPriority.description: Enables prioritized frames based on there IEEE priority tags. Set to 1 for enable and 0 for disable.

geCPUPortIPQoSPriority.name: geCPUPortIPQoSPriority
geCPUPortIPQoSPriority.description: Enables prioritized frames based on their IP4/IP6 priority fields. Set to 1 for enable and 0 for disable.

geCPUPortQoSPortMapRule.name: geCPUPortQoSPortMapRule
geCPUPortQoSPortMapRule.description: Forces queue priority for a port. Set to 1 for enable and 0 for disable.

geCPUPortVIDNRLEnable.name: geCPUPortVIDNRLEnable
geCPUPortVIDNRLEnable.description: Enables/disables per port the Non rate limit for VLANs with the NRL bit enabled. Set to 1 for enable and 0 for disable.

geCPUPortDisablePIRL2Bucket.name: geCPUPortDisablePIRL2Bucket
geCPUPortDisablePIRL2Bucket.description: Disables per port an already defined Port Ingress Rate Limitation (PIRL) bucket, input parameter bucket 0 - 4.

geCPUPortEgressRateLimitation.name: geCPUPortEgressRateLimitation
geCPUPortEgressRateLimitation.description: Sets the egress limitation rate for the port. Input parameter is value in kbps

geCPUPortIngressRateLimitation.name: geCPUPortIngressRateLimitation
geCPUPortIngressRateLimitation.description: Sets a Port Input Rate Limit(PIRL) bucket. Input parameters are: bucket:rate:layer:(DROP|FC)

geCPUPortDefaultVLAN.name: geCPUPortDefaultVLAN
geCPUPortDefaultVLAN.description: Sets the default VLAN ID(VID) for the port. Input parameter is 0 - 4095

geCPUPortForceDefaultVID.name: geCPUPortForceDefaultVID
geCPUPortForceDefaultVID.description: Forces the tagging of VID on all frames on the port. Set to 1 for enable and 0 for disable.

geCPUPortVLANPortMode.name: geCPUPortVLANPortMode
geCPUPortVLANPortMode.description: Sets the 802.1Q mode for the ingress port. Mode either 0=disable, 1=fallback, 2=check, 3=secure

geCPUPortBlockAllUnknown.name: geCPUPortBlockAllUnknown
geCPUPortBlockAllUnknown.description: This will make sure that all frames received on the port are blocked, unless they are tagged with the correct VID.

geCPUPortIGMPSnooping.name: geCPUPortIGMPSnooping
geCPUPortIGMPSnooping.description: Enables/disables IGMP snooping. Set to 1 for enable and 0 for disable.

geCPUPortAddUnicast.name: geCPUPortAddUnicast
geCPUPortAddUnicast.description: Adds the unicast mac address statically to the Address Translation Unit (ATU) Switch table. Input parameter is: aa:bb:cc:dd:ee:ff

geCPUPortAddMulticast.name: geCPUPortAddMulticast
geCPUPortAddMulticast.description: Adds the IP multicast address statically to the Address Translation Unit (ATU) Switch table. Input parameter is: aaa.bbb.ccc.ddd

geCPUPortMtu.name: geCPUPortMtu
geCPUPortMtu.description: The MTU size of the port.
